Package com.microsoft.azure.management.resources.fluentcore.arm.collection

Interface SupportsGettingByName<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the resource collection
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AaaaRecordSets, ActiveDirectoryApplications, ActiveDirectoryGroups, ActiveDirectoryUsers, ARecordSets, AuthorizationRules<RuleT>, BatchAIJobs, CaaRecordSets, CNameRecordSets, ConnectionMonitors, Deployments, DeploymentSlots, DnsRecordSets<RecordSetT>, ExpressRouteCircuitPeerings, FunctionDeploymentSlots, MXRecordSets, NamespaceAuthorizationRules, NSRecordSets, PacketCaptures, PolicyDefinitions, Providers, PtrRecordSets, QueueAuthorizationRules, Queues, ResourceGroups, ServiceBusSubscriptions, ServicePrincipals, SrvRecordSets, SupportsGettingByNameAsync<T>, TopicAuthorizationRules, Topics, TxtRecordSets, VirtualNetworkGatewayConnections

    public interface SupportsGettingByName<T>
    Provides access to getting a specific Azure resource based on its name within the current resource group.

    (Note this interface is not intended to be implemented by user code.)

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      T getByName​(java.lang.String name)
      Gets the information about a resource from Azure based on the resource name within the current resource group.

        Gets the information about a resource from Azure based on the resource name within the current resource group.
